it] common northern portion florida, underground springs feed water everglades system. underground reservoir called floridan aquifer lies 1,000 feet (300m) surface south florida.[17] everglades immense capacity water storage, owing permeable limestone beneath exposed land. water arrives form rainfall, significant amount stored limestone. water evaporating everglades becomes rain metropolitan areas, providing fresh water supply region. water also flows park falling rain north onto watersheds kissimmee river other sources lake okeechobee, appear everglades days later. water overflows lake okeechobee river 40 70 miles (110km) wide, moves almost imperceptibly.[18] everglades national park tropical savanna climate (köppen climate classification: aw) tropical monsoon climate (köppen climate classification: am), depending location. central region savanna climate, regions closer shore—especially eastern quarter park—has monsoonal climate. climates characterized two seasons: wet dry. park's dry season lasts december april, temperatures vary 53°f (12°c) 77°f (25°c) humidity low. since water levels low time, animals congregate central water locations, providing popular opportunities viewing wildlife.[19] wet season, may november, temperatures consistently 90°f (33°c) humidity times exceed 90percent.[20] storms drop 10 12 inches (300mm) rain time, providing half year's average 60inches (152cm) rainfall two months.[21] climate data flamingo ranger station, fl month jan feb mar apr may jun jul aug sep oct nov dec year average high °f (°c) 76.6 (24.8) 78.1 (25.6) 79.6 (26.4) 83.0 (28.3) 86.6 (30.3) 88.9 (31.6) 90.0 (32.2) 90.4 (32.4) 89.3 (31.8) 86.6 (30.3) 82.4 (28) 78.5 (25.8) 84.17 (28.96) average low °f (°c) 56.4 (13.6) 59.0 (15) 61.2 (16.2) 64.2 (17.9) 69.8 (21) 74.5 (23.6) 75.2 (24) 75.4 (24.1) 74.7 (23.7) 70.7 (21.5) 64.8 (18.2) 59.7 (15.4) 67.13 (19.52) average precipitation inches (mm) 1.70 (43.2) 1.73 (43.9) 1.99 (50.5) 1.84 (46.7) 3.49 (88.6) 7.18 (182.4) 5.60 (142.2) 7